name: Saint Paul VI Institute
description: The Saint Paul VI Institute is a research, education, medical, and service center that provides healthy, moral solutions to women's health care issues through the Creighton Model FertilityCare™ System and NaProTechnology. They offer services for infertility, PMS, ovarian cysts, recurrent miscarriage, abnormal bleeding, polycystic ovarian disease, menstrual cramps, endometriosis, and irregular cycles

name: FertilityCare Center of Omaha – Saint Paul VI Institute
description: This center offers individualized teaching of the CREIGHTON MODEL FertilityCare™ System charting to naturally regulate fertility and menstrual cycles to achieve or avoid pregnancy, and for NaProTECHNOLOGY diagnosis and treatment

name: Creighton Model FertilityCare Center of the Heartland
description: Offers Creighton Model FertilityCare System services, which use mucus observation to identify fertility and infertility. This method works with NaProTechnology for women's health issues

name: Good Counsel FertilityCare Center
description: Provides services related to the Creighton Model FertilityCare System, which can be used to achieve or avoid pregnancy and address various women's health conditions

name: White Lily FertilityCare Center
description: Offers FertilityCare services using the Creighton Model, which helps in identifying fertile and infertile times for natural family planning and addressing reproductive health concerns

name: Catholic Charities of the Archdiocese of Omaha, Inc. - Adoption Services
description: Provides adoption services, working with prospective adoptive families and birth parents to create adoption plans. They serve families throughout the Archdiocese of Omaha and surrounding areas

name: Catholic Social Services Lincoln
address: 8101 O St, Suite S-111, Lincoln, NE 68510
description: Offers adoption services and counseling, including pregnancy and adoption counseling, family, individual, and marital counseling

name: Catholic Charities of Omaha
description: Provides a wide range of services including adoption information and services, abuse recovery, affordable housing, and support for those suffering

name: Sancta Familia Medical Apostolate
description: A Catholic Medical Apostolate providing healthcare for the whole family, including fertility care for women and support for mothers and their unborn babies

name: MyCatholicDoctor (featuring various clinicians)
address: Various locations and virtual services available
description: This platform connects patients with Catholic healthcare providers, including those specializing in fertility care and women's health from a Catholic perspective. Dr. David Wachs has a special interest in infertility care and family planning
